.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B docs \fR[\fITOPIC\fR]
Built-in docs (\fBs docs pmap\fR, \fBs docs '|>'\fR).
Drops into a TUI hover-doc reader with vi-style navigation
(\fBj/k\fR next/prev, \fBd/u\fR \[+-]5, \fB]/[\fR chapter, \fBt\fR toc,
\fB/\fR search, \fB:\fIN\fR jump, \fBr\fR random, \fB?\fR help, \fBq\fR quit).
.TP
.B repl \fR[\fB--load \fIFILE\fR]
Interactive REPL with optional pre-load.
.TP
.B serve \fR[\fIPORT\fR] [\fISCRIPT\fR]
HTTP server (\fBs serve\fR, \fBs serve 8080 app.stk\fR).
.TP
.B fmt \fR[\fB-i\fR] \fIFILE\fR...
Format source files (\fBs fmt -i .\fR for in-place recursive).
.TP
.B bench \fR[\fIFILE|DIR\fR]
Run benchmarks from \fIbench/\fR or \fIbenches/\fR.
.TP
.B init \fR[\fINAME\fR]
Scaffold project in cwd: \fIstryke.toml\fR + \fIlib/\fR, \fIt/\fR, \fIbenches/\fR.
.TP
.B new \fINAME\fR
Scaffold a new project at \fI./NAME/\fR.
.TP
.B install \fR[\fB--offline\fR]
Resolve manifest deps; populate \fIstryke.lock\fR and \fI~/.stryke/store\fR.
.TP
.B add \fINAME\fR[\fB@\fIVER\fR] ...
Add a dep to \fIstryke.toml\fR. Flags:
.B --dev \fR/\fR --group=\fIN\fR \fR/\fR --path=\fIDIR\fR \fR/\fR --features=\fIA,B\fR.
.TP
.B remove \fINAME\fR
Drop a dep from \fIstryke.toml\fR; reruns install.
.TP
.B tree
Print resolved dep graph from \fIstryke.lock\fR.
.TP
.B info \fINAME\fR
Show lockfile entry + store path for a dep.
.TP
.B pkg \fISUBCOMMAND\fR
Dispatcher for package commands (init/new/install/add/remove/tree/info).
.TP
.B build \fISCRIPT\fR \fR[\fB-o \fIOUT\fR]
AOT: copy this binary with SCRIPT embedded (standalone exe).
.TP
.B --lsp
Language Server (JSON-RPC on stdio); must be the only argument.
.TP
.B --remote-worker
Persistent cluster worker (stdio); only argument.
.TP
.B --remote-worker-v1
Legacy one-shot worker (stdio); only argument.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PERL5LIB
Colon-separated list of dirs prepended to
.BR @INC .
.TP
.B PERL5OPT
Default command-line options.
.TP
.B STRYKE_RECORD
If set to \fB1\fR, records every run to \fI~/.stryke/perf.sqlite\fR for
later inspection via the \fBperfview\fR builtin.
.TP
.B STRYKE_AI_MODE
\fBmock-only\fR forces AI builtins to return mocked responses (for
tests). Pair with \fBai_mock_install\fR.
.TP
.B STRYKE_AUDIT_LOG
Path for the structured-audit JSONL append-log; default
\fI~/.stryke/audit.log\fR.
.TP
.B HOME
Used by \fBcd\fR (no args) and \fI~/.stryke\fR resolution.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.cargo/bin/s
Default install location via \fBcargo install strykelang\fR.
.TP
.I ~/.stryke/
Per-user state: \fBstore/\fR (dep blobs), \fBperf.sqlite\fR (run log),
\fBaudit.log\fR (JSONL audit), \fBscripts.db\fR (bytecode cache).
.TP
.I ./stryke.toml
Per-project manifest (deps, features, package metadata).
.TP
.I ./stryke.lock
Per-project lockfile (resolved dep graph + content hashes).
.TP
.I ./lib/
Project library code (loaded via \fBuse\fR / \fBrequire\fR).
.TP
.I ./t/
Test suite directory (run via \fBs t\fR).
.TP
