Every name stryke knows is in one of these compile-time-populated
hashes, queryable at the REPL with \fBkeys %\fIHASH\fR:
.PP
.RS 4
.B %b
.RB "\(em " "10,296 primary builtins (callable-only)"
.br
.B %a
.RB "\(em " "641 aliases (name \(-> primary)"
.br
.B %all
.RB "\(em " "11,022 keys: %b + %a + %k"
.br
.B %k
.RB "\(em " "85 keywords (if/while/sub/...)"
.br
.B %pc
.RB "\(em " "185 Perl 5 core names (subset of %b)"
.br
.B %e
.RB "\(em " "10,082 stryke extension names (subset of %b)"
.br
.B %d
.RB "\(em " "4,228 names with LSP hover documentation"
.br
.B %c
.RB "\(em " "306 distinct category strings"
.br
.B %p
.RB "\(em " "8,790 primaries (after alias dedup)"
.br
.B %o
.RB "\(em " "70 operators"
.br
.B %v
.RB "\(em " "97 special variables ($_, $!, @ARGV, %ENV, ...)"
.br
.B %parameters
.RB "\(em " "live binding view (every named pad slot)"
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
One-liner sum from stdin:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
seq 1 100 | s -ne '$s += $_; END { p $s }'
.EE
.RE
.PP
Parallel SHA-256 of 10000 files:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
s 'glob("**/*.txt") |> pmap { sha256 _ } |> e p'
.EE
.RE
.PP
Inline call to a builtin as a CLI tool (no script needed):
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
s basename /a/b/c.txt    # prints: c.txt
s sha256 myfile          # prints SHA-256 digest
s len 'hello'            # prints: 5
.EE
.RE
.PP
Format JSON from a URL:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
s 'curl_get("https://api.example.com/data") |> from_json |> to_table |> p'
.EE
.RE
.PP
Parallel grep with progress bar:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
s 'glob("logs/*.log") |> pmap { grep /ERROR/, read_lines _ } |> e p, progress => 1'
.EE
.RE
.PP
Scaffold a new project + add a dep:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
s new myproj && cd myproj
s add stryke-utils
.EE
.RE
.PP
Build a standalone binary that bundles a script:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
s build mytool.stk -o ./mytool
./mytool                 # runs without stryke installed
.EE
.RE
.PP
Drop into the REPL with a project pre-loaded:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
s repl --load ./lib/utils.stk
.EE
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
